cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the generation of realistic images of fine-grained object categories using an unsupervised GAN framework. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), which deals with image processing and computer vision. The paper also involves the use of information theory to associate each factor to a latent code, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of unsupervised learning to discover fine-grained object categories, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of hierarchical generation, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves clustering real images, which falls under the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
